German-sounding dialect:

SOUND CHANGES:

- Syllable-final -k turn into -kh
- S in clusters turns in to C
- Unstressed e becomes i between consonants, unchanged in front of word, changed into e (schwa) in end
- Unstressed a becomes a (lower schwa)
- When the next syllable has a long vowel, shorten it. Delete the vowel if possible, otherwise umlaut the vowel:
    o -> ö
    u -> ü
    a -> ä
    Else -> don't change
- All long vowels are shortened as follows:
    ē -> ei -> ai
    ā -> akh
    ō -> o
    ū -> u
    ī -> ei
    ai -> oü (Gm. "eu")	
    ei -> ai
    oi -> au
    ui -> ü
- voice consonant when it is on a stressed syllable unless it originally carried a long vowel
- VsV -> VzV
- ty -> tc
- sy -> c
- ky -> tc
- py -> pf
- w -> v
- th -> ss between non-back vowels, otherwise ts
- dh -> dr
- nt -> nd
- nd -> d
- mp -> mb
- mb -> b
- nVt/d -> nt
- mVp/b -> mp
- (l/r/y)(a/o) -> (l/r/y)

GRAMMAR:

Verbs almost fusional. Three tenses. Aspect and all the other junk uses helping verbs. insert e after stem if cluster is illegal.

PRESENT:

  S	P
1 -no	-nau
2 -nu	-nü
3 -n	-nakh

PAST:

  S	P
1 -to	-tau
2 -tu	-tü
3 -te	-ce

FUTURE:

  S	P
1 -sso	-ssau
2 -ssu	-ssü
3 -sse	-sse

Substantive using helping word sim before the verb. Attributive uses ben before the word. "laikh ben talyatess" = "talyate lēk"

Regular 1 declension (-V):
  NOM: RV	RV-len +umlaut on stressed
  DAT: -kh	-khen +umlaut
  ACC: -c	-lac
  (RV = remove final V)

First irregular declension (-im):
  NOM: -im	-ir
  DAT: -in	-ine +umlaut
  ACC: -is	-isai

Second irregular declension (-an):
  NOM: -an	-en + umlaut
  DAT: -af	-ef + umlaut
  ACC: -ac	-ec + umlaut
  
Lante aifakōranaroka,
marime uripa hessita.
Asela tilon arin akinita
Kelin nen tēritoi hassinaroka.
  Ka aifekoranar ben latess
  Uripe ben marimess heste
  Asil tilokh arikh ekinte
  sin kelessau tairetau ka nar ben hac.

Na-aifakōranaroka kai,
Asela hessi numavin-da.
Lante aifakōrame kitan
tathemāna navin na-kōra